The 27-year-old dancehall musician Stephen Kudzanai Mamhere, popularly known as Enzo Ishall, has hinted at plans to quit the music scene in 2021. In an Instagram post, he said that his last offering will be dropped on September 1, 2021. He however did not disclose his future plans. The singer rose to fame in 2018 with hit track Kanjiva, dominating the airwaves. He churned out several chart-topping tracks including; Smart Rinotangira Kutsoka, 50 Magate and Mhamha, among others that have done exceptionally well on the local music scene.